File Ownership and Permission

#You can change user ownership of files with: chown user /path/to/file
#You can change user and group ownership of files with: chown user:group /path/to/file
#You can change group ownership of files with: chown .user /path/to/file

PERMISSION
- |rwx| -rw- |r

First section: File type: usually - for regular, d for directory, l for link
Second section: User permission
Third section: Group permission
Last section: World permission

r:read, w:write, e:execute, -:not applied

CHANGING PERMISSION
#You can change file permission with: chmod +x /filename.sh   :to execute

